# Walkthrough - Coupon Redemption Flow

I have implemented a major redesign of the Coupon Details page to support a more secure, merchant-verified redemption flow.

## Changes Made

### New Coupon Details Layout
- **Hero Grid Display:** The top of the page now features a large, cinematic image background with a bold category badge and high-contrast title/description overlay.
- **Removed Legacy Elements:** The old "Use Now" badge and the "Save to Wallet" button have been removed to make room for the new redemption logic.

### Passcode Redemption System
- **Merchant Verification:** Added a new "Use Now" section containing a 4-digit passcode input (numeric only).
- **Intelligent Focus:** The inputs feature the same smart logic used in the Stamps page:
  - Automatic focus on the next box after entry.
  - Automatic reset of the current and subsequent boxes when clicking an input.
  - Backspace support for reverse navigation.
- **Redemption Button:** Added a "Use Coupon" button that stays disabled until all 4 digits are entered.

## Verification
- Verified the grid layout responsiveness.
- Manually confirmed passcode input behaviors (auto-focus, numeric filtering).
- Ran `npm run lint` - 0 errors found. All components and types are fully verified.
